title: Ceiling Medallion, 1875–1906
creditline: Museum purchase from Smithsonian Institution Collections Acquisition Program and Sarah Cooper-Hewitt Funds
description:
Wallpaper roll. 
One half of a circular ceiling medallion: central floral motif within a half circle. This is set within a larger triangle shape containing pink and blue flowers. Gold corners extend beyond this triangle, containing pink flowers. Pink circular line encloses entire medallion.
